Reason: The original grouped+unstack approach sometimes left tied counts in an arbitrary order (because sort_values is unstable by default), whereas pandas.value_counts() breaks ties by sorting labels ascending. By adding a secondary sort on discourse_type we reproduce the exact row order. We also explicitly mask counts_last==0 to NaN (and propagate that into percent_last) so the output matches the original left-merge behavior.
